Vibium Contribution Framework: Volunteer vs. Compensated

To maintain the health of the Vibium ecosystem, we draw a clear line between Community Growth (Ambassador/Volunteer) and Core Engineering/Operations (Paid/Compensated).

🟠 The Volunteer Sphere (Ambassadors & MVPs)

Purpose: Community health, advocacy, and organic growth.
Rewards: Leaderboard points, exclusive merch, private beta access, speaking slots, and "Vibium Credits" (non-monetary recognition).

1. Educational Content

Community Tutorials: Writing "How-to" guides on personal blogs or Dev.to.

Explainer Videos: Creating short-form clips or "Day in the Life of an Agent" videos.

Social Advocacy: Engaging with the #AgenticWeb community on X/Twitter.

2. Peer Support & Mentorship

Discord Moderation: Helping newcomers set up their first Vibium instance.

Issue Triaging: Clarifying bug reports and helping users find existing solutions.

Community Calls: Hosting or speaking at informal community hangouts.

3. Open Ecosystem Growth

Third-Party Plugins: Building "fun" or niche connectors for the community.

Local Meetups: Organizing small "Agent & Coffee" meetups in local cities.

Documentation Polish: Fixing typos or clarifying language in public docs.

🔘 The Compensated Sphere (Bounty & Contract)

Purpose: High-reliability core infrastructure, security, and critical path items.
Rewards: Direct USD/USDC payments, formal contracts, or significant grants.

1. Core Protocol Engineering

Security Hardening: Deep-dive audits or patching critical vulnerabilities.

Architectural Refactors: Major performance overhauls that require 20+ hours of focused deep-work.

Official SDK Maintenance: Managing the official release cycles for core libraries.

2. High-Value Technical Assets

Enterprise Benchmarking: Running complex, long-term performance stress tests for official whitepapers.

Official Documentation Architecture: Designing the structure and technical deep-dives of the official docs site.

Core Feature Bounties: Completing specific high-priority roadmap items tagged with a bounty.

3. Professional Representation

Official Workshop Lead: Being hired to represent Vibium at major global conferences (Sponsorship + Speaking Fee).

Technical Consulting: Helping official Vibium partners integrate the protocol into their stack.

🚦 The "Danger Zone" (When to move from Volunteer to Paid)

